The paper deals with the algorithmic aspects of temporal graphs, which are graphs whose edges are labeled with time stamps. This makes it likely that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper investigates the computational complexity of finding separators in temporal graphs, which is a problem that is closely related to graph theory and network analysis. This makes it likely that the paper also belongs to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. Furthermore, the paper uses fixed-parameter tractability (FPT) as a tool to analyze the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses empirical observations to distinguish between different models of temporal separation, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
